Description: Cylinder seal of black steatite: perforated through the centre, bearing a well-preserved inscription in incised hieroglyphs. Good condition.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl. 98, abb. 411; A. Sayce, ‘Proceedings of the Society of Biblical Archaeology’ 22 (London, 1900), 279 and pl. opp. p.278, (2).
